parameter.name: help_in_main_menu_command
parameter.answer: The value can be any command or selection number that triggers the instructions, for example: 'Help' or '1'. This value should correspond to the code in main_menu.html and help.py.

parameter.name: expected_output
parameter.answer: The expected output when the player input help command in the main menu. This value should be generated based on the display_help() function in help.py.

parameter.name: wrong_command
parameter.answer: The value should be any invalid command or selection number that does not correspond to any legitimate action, for example: 'invalid-command'. This value should be used to check if an incorrect command is handled gracefully by the application.

parameter.name: expected_output
parameter.answer: The expected output when the player input a wrong selection in the main menu. This value may vary based on the specific context of the application.

parameter.name: start_command
parameter.answer: The value should be any command or selection number that starts the game, for example: 'New Game' or 'Play'. This value should correspond to the code in main_menu.html.

parameter.name: expected_output
parameter.answer: The expected output when the player start the game. This value should be generated based on the appropriate function related to starting a new game.

parameter.name: help_in_game
parameter.answer: The value can be any command that triggers the instructions related to the commands available within the game, for example: '?' or 'help'. This value should correspond to the code in the game.

parameter.name: expected_output
parameter.answer: The expected output when the player input the help command in the game. This value should be generated based on the display_help() function within the game.

parameter.name: expected_output
parameter.answer: The expected output when the player input the command ls. This value should be generated based on the look-around function in the game.

parameter.name: direction
parameter.answer: A legitimate direction based on the current context of the game, for example: 'north' or '../../home'. Assume that the player just got into the game and did nothing.

parameter.name: expected_output
parameter.answer: The expected output when the player input a legitimate direction to move. This value may vary based on the specific context of the application.
